wolf.Description: a feral wolf residing in the forest
wolf.Name: wolf

bear.Description: a quite fluffy, if not deadly creature residing in the forest
bear.Name: bear

fae.Description: a magical being that spends its free time playing tricks on humans
fae.Name: fae

zombie.Description: a dead person brought back by dark and insidious magic
zombie.Name: zombie

werewolf.Description: a person altered by a dark curse, forever fated to walk the earth as part man, part wolf
werewolf.Name: werewolf

skeleton warrior.Description: a long dead warrior brought back once more for a final battle
skeleton warrior.Name: skeleton warrior

skeleton archer.Description: a long dead warrior brought back once more for a final battle, he was once quite proficient with a bow
skeleton archer.Name: skeleton archer

boar.Description: a wild pig with long sharp tusks
boar.Name: boar

litch.Description: an undead spell caster who sought eternal life when alive. he got his wish, just not in the way he had hoped
litch.Name: litch

bandit.Description: a man down on his luck, resorting to murder and theivery
bandit.Name: bandit

bandit captain.Description: A bandit who has been in the buisness for years and had climed the ranks and is now at the top of the deck
bandit captain.Name: bandit captain

ghost.Description: a dead spirit brought back by unfinished buisness to haunt the mortal realm
ghost.Name: ghost

valupuir.Description: a lesser vampire that can go into sunlight but is weaker than a pureblood. mostly act as servants to pure vampires
valupuir.Name: valupuir

valupire.Description: a lesser vampire that has an aversion to sunlight. stronger than valupuir
valupire.Name: valupire

valupire captain.Description: a lesser vampire with an aversion to sunlight. this valupire has proved its worth to its master, and will soon ascend to become a vampire
valupire captain.Name: valupire captain

vampire.Description: a vampire that lives off the blood of other creatures if it were to encounter sunlight it would be greatly harmed. vampires usually lead their respective groups, however there is one above them...
vampire.Name: vampire

cain.Description: the first murderer in the world, after he killed his brother, able he was punished to eternal suffering by forever having to walk the earth and the need to feed on the innocent, and turn others to monsters like him.
cain.Name: cain

goblin.Description: a small green creature that is incredibly weak
goblin.Name: goblin

spiderling.Description: a hatchling mega-spider about the size of a human head, even newly hatched they are very deadly. thankfully their venom glands are not developed yet.
spiderling.Name: spiderling

juvenile mega-spider.Description: a larger more dangerous version of the spiderling, its exoskeleton has hardened and its venom glands are working. do not get bit.
juvenile mega-spider.Name: juvenile mega-spider

adult mega spider.Description: a fully matured version of a mega-spider, its exoskeleton is nigh impenetrable and its venom the most potent of them all. yet even this being bows to something.
adult mega spider.Name: adult mega spider

Arachne.Description: the first spider. once human she angered a god with her talent in weaving and her beauty. because of this she was turned into a horrible monster. standing on 8 legs and 9.5 feet tall towering even over her largest subjects, her hate for humanity has caused them to be her primary prey
Arachne.Name: Arachne
